🎨 Physical Layout Design & Verification
The physical layout of the differential amplifier's lower matching stage was implemented 
using the open-source Magic VLSI layout engine and the SkyWater 130nm (sky130) process node. 
The layout directly translates the schematic netlist into a manufacturable, DRC-clean physical architecture.

📐 Layout Topology & Device Sizing
Target Core: Differential pair / Current mirror active load (M5 and M6 transistors).

Matching Interleaving Strategy: A split-finger layout topology arranged in an abccba / M6-M6-M5-M5-M5-M5-M6-M6 configuration.

Purpose: Implementing this interdigitated configuration drastically reduces mismatch caused by cross-chip thermal gradients and linear process variations, ensuring tight parameter symmetry between the balanced nodes.
